data.content: When was the last ICC worldcup played

The last ICC Men's Cricket World Cup was played in 2023. It was held in India, and Australia won the tournament, defeating India in the final. The tournament started on October 5th and concluded on November 19th. There were a total of 48 matches played across 10 different venues in India. The top run-scorer of the tournament was Virat Kohli, and the top wicket-taker was Mohammed Shami.
